-- Square in talks for $200 mln funding - Bloomberg
-- By Arnab Sen in Bangalore
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 03:42AM EDT
-- None



Aug 28 (Reuters) - Mobile payment startup Square Inc, co-founded by Twitter Inc <TWTR.N> Chairman Jack Dorsey, is in talks to raise $200 million, at a valuation of $6 billion, Bloomberg reported, citing a person with knowledge of the matter.

Some of the funding is expected to come from the Government of Singapore Investment Corp (GIC), which will push Square's valuation up from about $5 billion earlier this year, the report said. (http://bloom.bg/1vSCPX6) Square and GIC were not immediately available for comment.